  "event_preview": "The Detroit Street Circuit is a 1.645-mile (2.647 km) temporary 14-turn circuit in downtown Detroit, Michigan, running through the streets near the downtown core and past the Renaissance Center. The Chevrolet Detroit Grand Prix is the eighth round of the 2026 NTT IndyCar Series season, contested over 100 laps (164.5 miles). Kyle Kirkwood is the defending winner after claiming victory in the 2025 running at this venue.\n\nÁlex Palou leads the championship standings heading into the weekend, with Kyle Kirkwood looking to make up ground after his strong early-season start that included a victory on the streets of Arlington, Texas. Kirkwood enters Detroit as one of the most accomplished street racers on the current IndyCar grid and arrives seeking to build momentum following a competitive run on the compact Detroit circuit. Will Power, a veteran with multiple street course wins, will be seeking to climb the standings after a slower start to the 2026 season. Chevrolet's global headquarters overlook this circuit from Hudson, Detroit, giving the Detroit race special significance for the manufacturer's representation in the series.\n\nThe all-time qualifying record at the Detroit Street Circuit belongs to Colton Herta, who set a 1:00.4779 in the Firestone Fast Six during the 2025 running. The race lap record is held by Kyle Kirkwood, who clocked a 1:01.9410 during the 2023 race.",
